SIMPLE: serviceable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serviceable
<hw>Serv"ice*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Doing service; promoting happiness, interest, advantage, or any
good; useful to any end; adapted to any good end use; beneficial;
advantageous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Serviceable</xex> to religion and
learning⟦rdquo⟧. <au>Atterbury.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Serviceable</xex>
tools.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know thee well, a <qex>serviceable</qex> villain.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Prepared for rendering service; capable of, or fit
for, the performance of duty; hence, active; diligent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Courteous he was, lowly, and <qex>servysable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bright-hearnessed angels sit in order <qex>serviceable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seeing her so sweet and <qex>serviceable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennnyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Serv"ice*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Serv"ice*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serviceage</ent>⟦br⟧
